For Hu Ming, there was no time to watch the news of the epidemic, not even the Spring Festival gala, New Year's Eve or the first day of the Lunar New Year, to send a New Year message to his colleagues. Busy with the treatment of critically ill patients, he often had to work until two or three in the morning to eat a meal, a day can only rest for two or three hours.

The Wuhan Lung Hospital, where he worked, was the real frontline in the fight against pneumonia, the first designated hospital for COVID-19 pneumonia, specializing in the treatment of critically ill patients.

Hu Ming is the director of the ICU, where the department every day and the virus, and death wage a tug of war, every day is a war without gunpowder smoke.

He was accompanied by a doctor in a protective suit who held his breath for hours without drinking water or going to the bathroom; a nurse who monitored patients on the ward; a pharmacy worker who was still in the early 30s and was urgently stockpiling drugs; It's the bride-to-be who pushed the wedding off.

He said he treated cases, a patient, a person infected with several people, and a colleague said, his treatment of severe patients have died, may also be less serious treatment.

In an interview with the Xiaoxiang Morning Post, Hu said that the tragic death of a retired doctor he knew from the school was heartbreaking, saying that after the outbreak, the unit sent him to the front line, but he didn't expect it.

"I think of my 9-year-old children and my wife in distress, who were my closest friends during SARS. "

She had to go out and ask for this, ask for that, everyone was fighting for things, asking for this, asking for that, and then there were dozens of patients in there, taking baths, scheduling shifts, and she hadn't seen her daughter either.

Feng told me years ago, she said to take three days off to go home with her daughter. I said yes. Take three days off. Later, a refund, I said you refund why, I also thought that two weeks before New Year's Eve done.

We also have a doctor, before the Spring Festival said to prepare to get married, and then she told the bridegroom official said, you see, it is estimated that we can not go out, or put it off.

【19】

It's nice to be recognized by the patient and his family

It's hard, it's the right thing to do, it's hard work, it's stressful, it's okay, or what?

In fact, we are most happy when what is the matter, really is the patient discharged or alleviate the symptoms.

We have the first confirmed patient here, from the Intensive Care Unit to the general ward to live, ICU here within half a month three patients out of the general ward, now is it.

The first patient we treated was a guy from the countryside, and it didn't look like things were going so well at home, like a storekeeper or something, how much do you think you could make in a month.

When I came here, I was in a hurry. I wasn't sure if it was this disease, but I suspected it was this disease.

As a result, he was resuscitated and discharged from the hospital. When he was ready to be discharged from the hospital, his family seemed to be waiting at the door with a large pile of oranges and fruits and a large package. Indeed, he was very grateful. He waited for several hours.

As a result, while we were pushing the bed out, pushing the new patient, we were in a hurry.

When you're a doctor, especially when you're a very sick doctor, you bring someone back to life, and you enjoy the feeling, the accomplishment.

You know, the recognition, the recognition. Maybe that's what you want when you save someone's life, to be recognized by someone else.

It's a real thank you, and unlike the polite way of saying it, you get a real sense of approval just for that. What do you think a doctor wants? Just for a little bit, for a good result.

【20】

Let's get through this together. Come on, Wuhan

After the third day of the first lunar month, medical and protective materials may be shipped into Wuhan, overtime a few days may be greatly eased. But if the epidemic is not brought under control soon, it will be in great demand.

In this regard, overseas students or through the introduction of the students, call to follow up, asked me if I want something, and then what is willing to bear, express how to go AH, etc. , are very active. Gives me a feeling of support from all sides, especially the warm feeling.

So many people, some know you, do not know you, to call you, to donate supplies, you say what, it is not said that money has no place to spend AH.

I don't even know who he is after I answer the phone, because he just says who I am and who introduced me to him, and I don't even know his last name.

These two days, there are sad stories, there are success stories, there are touching stories. I'VE WORKED AT INTENSIVE-CARE UNIT FOR MORE THAN 20 years, and I've seen a lot of it, but today I'm suddenly very emotional, and I don't know why.

In fact, we really work in the front line of people, busy to the end only want to hurry to cure a few patients, just want to save the lives of others, so simple.

We survived the Wenchuan County earthquake, we survived SARS, we survived bird flu. Through so many difficulties, I believe that as long as we are in the same boat, together through the difficult times, we will be able to get through.

This time also needs you media reporters, from a deeper perspective to promote something, so that we have more confidence, do not let panic more than the epidemic, to know that any disease can be prevented and controlled, even if there is no specific medicine in the short term.

Wuhan, come on. China, come on.
